<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> My dearest sister, and old friend,<br>
<br>
We need not amuse ourselves with small talk. You know of the invitations traveling the lands, and the names upon them. As each arrives at it's destination, the ripples in the water become waves. I fear for your good names, and that of your house. It is not my place to tell you or anyone else what to think, and I have kept my tongue this long, but you have many who care for you both, and we sincerely worry for you now. Please take care...<br>
<br>
~Bridh Triegean<br>
